# Architecture: FSD + SOLID

Follow [Feature-Sliced Design](https://feature-sliced.design/) and SOLID under `src/`. Prefer incremental alignment with FSD over big-bang rewrites.

## Layers (dependency flows down only)

| Layer | Maps to | Role |
|-------|---------|------|
| App | `main.tsx`, `App.tsx`, providers | Composition, routing shell |
| Pages | `pages/` | Screens; compose widgets/features; thin logic |
| Widgets | `components/*` | Composite UI blocks |
| Features | `features/<name>/` when a slice grows | User flows: UI + local state + calls into entities/shared |
| Entities | `types/`, domain models | Types and domain shape; no UI |
| Shared | `utils/`, `services/`, `state/`, `data/` | API clients, helpers, cross-cutting state |

**Imports:** Shared → no pages/widgets/features. Entities → shared only. Features → entities + shared. Pages → features, widgets, entities, shared. App → anything.

**Slices:** Group by capability (e.g. marketplace, auth), not only by file type. Colocate cohesive UI + model + API usage when it belongs together.

## SOLID (short)

- **S** — Split fat pages into hooks/components; one domain per service module.
- **O** — Extend via composition and new modules; use `data/` config where it fits.
- **L** — Types and `services/` mappers stay consistent with API contracts.
- **I** — Small props and service surfaces; avoid oversized context objects.
- **D** — Pages/components use typed `services/` and hooks, not scattered raw `fetch`.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ Page inlines fetch + JSON mapping
// ✅ Page uses services/ or a feature hook; types from types/

// ❌ utils/ imports a page
// ✅ Page imports utils/

// ❌ Shared component imports page-specific types
// ✅ Page passes data; shared stays generic
```

If a dependency points “up” the stack, **move logic down** (extract to shared/entities/feature) instead.
